<subSubSection id="FA905881FFF82E2826C7FF6FFED3FCB1" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B2350B0AFFF82E2826C7FF6FFED3FCB1" blockId="11.[151,1437,546,1905]" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E2826C7FF6FFEEAFD6B" bold="true" box="[199,322,618,644]" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be recognized by the following combination of characters: mandible with two teeth, antenna with 20 flagellomeres, scape predominantly yellowish brown, face and clypeus forming a continuous surface, pronotum with a single wrinkle arising from pronotal pit (
<figureCitation id="2AB1178FFFF82E282576FFB6FC63FD22" box="[886,971,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1654,1678]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,187,1631]" captionTargetId="figure-23@12.[151,1435,181,1631]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Details of Forrestopius runasimi, sp. nov. A. Habitus of female, in lateral view (scale bar = 1 mm) B. Propodeum and first metasomal tergite C. Pronotum, in lateral view D. Facial view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531263" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531263/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
) which upper end reaches about two third of way to anterior margin and dorso-posterior corner yellowish brown, propodeum with lateromedian and lateral longitudinal carinae (
<figureCitation id="2AB1178FFFF82E282784FFFEFE72FCFA" box="[388,474,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1654,1678]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,187,1631]" captionTargetId="figure-23@12.[151,1435,181,1631]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Details of Forrestopius runasimi, sp. nov. A. Habitus of female, in lateral view (scale bar = 1 mm) B. Propodeum and first metasomal tergite C. Pronotum, in lateral view D. Facial view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531263" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531263/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
), and metatarsomeres light brown (
<figureCitation id="2AB1178FFFF82E282561FFFEFC12FCFA" box="[865,954,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1654,1678]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,187,1631]" captionTargetId="figure-23@12.[151,1435,181,1631]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Details of Forrestopius runasimi, sp. nov. A. Habitus of female, in lateral view (scale bar = 1 mm) B. Propodeum and first metasomal tergite C. Pronotum, in lateral view D. Facial view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531263" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531263/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
). This species looks similar to 
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E28230DFFFEFE92FCD6" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">
<taxonomicName id="758A7089FFF82E28230DFFFEFF10FCD7" authorityName="Alvarado &amp; Palacio" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Forrestopius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auguratricis">F. auguratricis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="758A7089FFF82E2826C3FE1AFE92FCD6" authorityName="Alvarado &amp; Palacio" authorityYear="2021" box="[195,314,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Forrestopius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jumandi">F. jumandi</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="758A7089FFF82E28276EFE1AFE70FCD7" authorityName="Alvarado &amp; Palacio" authorityYear="2021" box="[366,472,799,824]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Forrestopius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yungas">
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E28276EFE1AFE70FCD7" box="[366,472,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">F. yungas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs from them by having the submetapleural carina smooth (vs. submetapleural carina scrobiculate).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FA905881FFF82E2826C7FE63FE2AF90E" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" type="description">
<paragraph id="B2350B0AFFF82E2826C7FE63FC77FC6E" blockId="11.[151,1437,546,1905]" box="[199,991,870,897]" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E2826C7FE63FE68FC6E" bold="true" box="[199,448,870,897]" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Description. Female:</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity id="7572A6EFFFF82E282458FE62FD19FC6E" box="[600,689,871,897]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.2" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" unit="mm" value="8.2">8.2 mm</quantity>
. Fore wing length 
<quantity id="7572A6EFFFF82E282582FE63FC73FC6E" box="[898,987,870,897]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B2350B0AFFF82E2826C7FE8EFA39FBB6" blockId="11.[151,1437,546,1905]" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E2826C7FE8EFEA3FC4A" box="[199,267,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Head.</emphasis>
Face and clypeus forming a continuous surface, 1.0× as long as wide, smooth with punctures, upper quarter weakly striate (
<figureCitation id="2AB1178FFFF82E282763FEAAFE13FC26" box="[355,443,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1654,1678]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,187,1631]" captionTargetId="figure-23@12.[151,1435,181,1631]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Details of Forrestopius runasimi, sp. nov. A. Habitus of female, in lateral view (scale bar = 1 mm) B. Propodeum and first metasomal tergite C. Pronotum, in lateral view D. Facial view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531263" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531263/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Fig. 7D</figureCitation>
); labrum not exposed when mandibles closed; mandibles with two teeth; malar space 1.2× as long as basal mandibular width; lateral ocellus separated from compound eye by about 1.1× maximum ocellar diameter; distance between ocelli 1.2× maximum ocellar diameter; vertex behind ocellar triangle slightly declivous, occiput concave; gena in lateral view 1.0× as long as compound eye; antenna with 20 flagellomeres, ratio of length from second to fourth flagellomeres: 0.7:0.7:0.7, subapical flagellomere elongate, 1.1× as long as centrally broad.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B2350B0AFFF82E2826C7F966FE15FA96" blockId="11.[151,1437,546,1905]" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E2826C7F966FEEFFB93" box="[199,327,1123,1148]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">
<taxonomicName id="758A7089FFF82E2826C7F966FEEAFB93" box="[199,322,1123,1148]" class="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" family="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" genus="Mesosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Mesosoma</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Pronotum with wrinkle arising from pronotal pit, its upper end reaching about two third of way to anterior margin (
<figureCitation id="2AB1178FFFF82E282753F982FE04FB4E" box="[339,428,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1654,1678]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,187,1631]" captionTargetId="figure-23@12.[151,1435,181,1631]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Details of Forrestopius runasimi, sp. nov. A. Habitus of female, in lateral view (scale bar = 1 mm) B. Propodeum and first metasomal tergite C. Pronotum, in lateral view D. Facial view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531263" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531263/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
); metapleuron polished with isolated setae, posteroventrally striate; submetapleural carina smooth, anteriorly expanded into triangular lobe. Propodeum with lateromedian longitudinal carina strong, slightly closer to each other anteriorly (
<figureCitation id="2AB1178FFFF82E2827FDF9CAFDFEFB06" box="[509,598,1231,1257]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1654,1678]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,187,1631]" captionTargetId="figure-23@12.[151,1435,181,1631]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Details of Forrestopius runasimi, sp. nov. A. Habitus of female, in lateral view (scale bar = 1 mm) B. Propodeum and first metasomal tergite C. Pronotum, in lateral view D. Facial view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531263" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531263/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
); lateral longitudinal carina complete; posterior transverse carina present; area superomedia+petiolaris 2.9× as long as wide. Fore wing with vein 
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E2825B0F9F6FC79FAE2" box="[944,977,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Cu</emphasis>
1 
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E2825DEF9F6FC44FAE3" box="[990,1004,1267,1292]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">a</emphasis>
between 
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E282256F9F6FBDFFAE2" box="[1110,1143,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Cu</emphasis>
1 
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E282285F9F6FB3BFAE2" box="[1157,1171,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">b</emphasis>
and 2 
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E2822D6F9F6FAA6FAE3" box="[1238,1294,1267,1292]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">m-cu</emphasis>
1.7× as long as 
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E2826B6F812FF7FFADE" box="[182,215,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Cu</emphasis>
1 between 
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E282750F812FEC4FADF" box="[336,364,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Rs</emphasis>
&amp; 
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E282782F812FE31FADF" box="[386,409,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">M</emphasis>
and 1 
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E2827DDF812FDBDFADF" box="[477,533,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">m-cu</emphasis>
; 2 
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E282432F812FDCDFADF" box="[562,613,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">rs-m</emphasis>
0.6× as long as abscissa of 
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E28259DF812FC1CFADF" box="[925,948,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">M</emphasis>
between 2 
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E28222EF812FBC9FADF" box="[1070,1121,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">rs-m</emphasis>
and 2 
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E2822A6F812FB76FADF" box="[1190,1246,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">m-cu</emphasis>
. Hind wing with distal abscissa of 
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E28275FF83EFEDEFABB" box="[351,374,1339,1364]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">M</emphasis>
indistinguishable, distal abscissa of 
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E282514F83EFC9DFABA" box="[788,821,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Cu</emphasis>
1 and 1 
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E282588F83EFC31FABA" box="[904,921,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">A</emphasis>
sclerotized throughout. Outer metatibial spur 0.7× as long as inner spur.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B2350B0AFFF82E2826C7F886FACDFA0A" blockId="11.[151,1437,546,1905]" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E2826C7F886FEEBFA73" box="[199,323,1411,1436]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Metasoma.</emphasis>
Tergite I 1.4× as long as posteriorly wide (
<figureCitation id="2AB1178FFFF82E282517F886FCC5FA72" box="[791,877,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1654,1678]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,187,1631]" captionTargetId="figure-23@12.[151,1435,181,1631]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Details of Forrestopius runasimi, sp. nov. A. Habitus of female, in lateral view (scale bar = 1 mm) B. Propodeum and first metasomal tergite C. Pronotum, in lateral view D. Facial view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531263" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531263/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
), lateromedian carina extending 0.5× length of tergite, smooth with isolated punctures on the apical half (absent centrally); tergite II 0.9× as long as posteriorly wide; laterotergite II 0.2× as wide as long; laterotergite III 0.5× as wide as long, wedge-shaped, mesal edge straight.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B2350B0AFFF82E2826C7F8EAFCE1F952" blockId="11.[151,1437,546,1905]" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E2826C7F8EAFEB3F9E6" box="[199,283,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Colour.</emphasis>
Head black, mandibles yellowish brown, scape, distal third of pedicel, and palpi yellow; basal 2/3 of pedicel and flagellomeres brown. 
<taxonomicName id="758A7089FFF82E282411FB16FD22F9C2" box="[529,650,1555,1581]" class="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" family="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" genus="Mesosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" pageId="11" pageNumber="279" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Mesosoma</taxonomicName>
black except dorso-posterior corner of pronotum yellowish brown and tegula yellow; fore and mid legs yellow, mid coxa dorsally light brown; hind leg with coxa and basal 2/3 of femur black, distal 1/3 of femur and basal 2/3 of tibia yellow; trochanter, trochantellus, 1/3 distal of tibia and tarsomeres light brown. Metasomal tergites dark brown with soft metallic blue reflection, metasomal tergites II–V distal margin and laterotergites brownish; ovipositor and valvae testaceous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B2350B0AFFF82E2826C7FBC2FE2AF90E" blockId="11.[151,1437,546,1905]" box="[199,386,1735,1761]" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E2826C7FBC2FEA5F90E" bold="true" box="[199,269,1735,1761]" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Male:</emphasis>
Unknown
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FA905881FFF82E2826C7FBEEFE29F8C6" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B2350B0AFFF82E2826C7FBEEFE29F8C6" blockId="11.[151,1437,546,1905]" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E2826C7FBEEFE93F8EA" bold="true" box="[199,315,1771,1797]" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was collected in a wet forest in 
<collectingCountry id="CA9D4B9AFFF82E282530FBEEFCCBF8EA" box="[816,867,1771,1797]" name="Peru" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Peru</collectingCountry>
at 
<quantity id="7572A6EFFFF82E282585FBEFFC7BF8EA" box="[901,979,1770,1797]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.52" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" unit="m" value="1520.0">1520m</quantity>
(
<figureCitation id="2AB1178FFFF82E2825E1FBEEFBE1F8EA" box="[993,1097,1771,1797]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="16.[151,250,881,905]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,857]" captionTargetId="figure-23@16.[151,1436,181,858]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 10. Geographic distribution of the Forrestopius species" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531269" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531269/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
); it occurs in the same locality as 
<taxonomicName id="758A7089FFF82E2826B6FA0AFE88F8C7" authority="Alvarado &amp; Palacio, 2021" authorityName="Alvarado &amp; Palacio" authorityYear="2021" box="[182,288,1807,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Forrestopius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yungas" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E2826B6FA0AFE88F8C7" box="[182,288,1807,1832]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">F. yungas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E282727FA0AFE29F8C6" bold="true" box="[295,385,1807,1833]" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9BCD6A63FFF82E282727FA0AFE29F8C6" box="[295,385,1807,1833]" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FA905881FFF82E2826C7FA36FE2BF89E" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="B2350B0AFFF82E2826C7FA36FE2BF89E" blockId="11.[151,1437,546,1905]" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E2826C7FA36FEE6F8A2" bold="true" box="[199,334,1843,1869]" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName id="758A7089FFF82E28243BFA36FD37F8A3" authorityName="Alvarado &amp; Palacio" authorityYear="2021" box="[571,671,1843,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Forrestopius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="runasimi">
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E28243BFA36FD37F8A3" box="[571,671,1843,1868]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">runasimi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
means ‘people’s language’ in the Quechua language. It is treated as a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
